CHONGLI -- Swiss skier Mathilde Gremaud, the runner-up at Pyeongchang 2018, claimed the women's freeski slopestyle gold at Beijing 2022 here on Tuesday. China's prodigy Gu Ailing, who beat Gremaud in the big air for the gold on Feb. 8, grabbed the silver with her third run score of 86.23 points. In the dramatic three-run final, Gremaud, 22, collapsed in the first section of her first run, receiving only 1.10 points as she was unable to perform in the other five sections of the run.